I"C<p>VirtualBox is a powerful opensource <a href="https://stechalon.com/virtualization-virtual-box-machine" target="_blank">virtualization</a> software or platform that provides you to manage and run multiple operating systems as an application at the same time. This masterpiece was developed by <a href="https://www.oracle.com/index.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Oracle Corporation</a> for enterprise-level and home use. In 2007 the software was invented by <a href="https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/innotek" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Innotek GmbH</a> and later acquired by Oracle in 2010.  This <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VirtualBox" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">application</a> supports multiple guest operating systems such as Linux, Windows, Solaris, Mac OS, Unices and <a href="https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Guest_OSes" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">others</a>.</p>

