<h1 id="installation">Installation</h1>
<h2 id="step-1-download-virtualbox">Step 1: Download VirtualBox</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Visit Oracle VirtualBox website <a href="https://www.virtualbox.org/" target="_blank">https://www.virtualbox.org/ </a> and go to the download as show in the picture below.</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/1.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Now select the Windows hosts platform.</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/2.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Save the Downlaod file.</strong></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Now download the extension pack. This helps you to connect your virtual machine with USB 2.0 and USB 3.0.</strong></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/3.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i> <b>Note:</b> Extension is not required to run VirtualBox. **This is optional**
</div>

