<h2 id="step-2-install-virtualbox">Step 2: Install VirtualBox</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Open and run the package from your Download directory.</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/4.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>You will see an installation window of VirtualBox. Click Next.</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/6.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Go to Browse if you want to install in different location or Next for defalut.</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/7.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Select the features for your desktop and Install.</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/10.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Click Finish after the installation is completed.</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/11.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<h2 id="step-3-setup-extension-in-virtualbox-optional">Step 3: Setup Extension in VirtualBox (Optional)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Run the application. Go to Files -&gt; Preferences -&gt; Extensions and Add the extension from your Download Folder.</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/12.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Select the extension</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/5.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Agree on the policy and complete the setup. Now you will be able to see similar as shown below</strong></li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-08-07/14.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<div class="bs-callout bs-callout-success">
    <h4>Congratulation!!</h4>
    Your installation is completed. Feel free to write me  if you face any problem.
</div>

